Salesforce.com, Inc. Issues Q2 2013 Guidance Revenue Guidance Above Analysts' Estimates; Raises FY 2013 Guidance
Thursday, 17 May 2012 04:05pm EDT
Salesforce.com, Inc. announced that for the second quarter of 2013, it expects revenue to be in the range of $724-$728 million. GAAP net loss per share is expected to be in the range of ($0.10)-($0.09), while diluted non-GAAP EPS is expected to be in the range of $0.38-$0.39. The non-GAAP estimate excludes the effects of stock-based compensation expense, expected to be approximately $85 million, amortization of purchased intangibles related to acquisitions, expected to be approximately $20 million, and net non-cash interest expense related to the convertible senior notes, expected to be approximately $6 million. For fiscal 2013, it expects revenue to be in the range of $2.97-$3.00 billion, GAAP net loss per share is expected to be in the range of ($0.48)-($0.45) while diluted non-GAAP EPS is expected to be in the range of $1.60 to $1.63. The non-GAAP estimate excludes the effects of stock-based compensation expense, expected to be approximately $366 million, amortization of purchased intangibles related to acquisitions, expected to be approximately $79 million, and net non-cash interest expense related to the convertible senior notes, expected to be approximately $24 million. According to I/B/E/S Estimates, analysts are expecting the Company to report revenues $714 million and EPS of $0.38 for the second quarter of 2013; revenues of $2.95 billion and EPS of $1.61 for fiscal 2013.Â 
